How to setup heads so they are auto booted with the rest of the things

Ok , so in order to make the heads work one must change the current bashrc madness and use a better way to boot them up 
 
So first copy the new scripts to the raspberry pi ..!
cd /opt/ros/hobbit_hydro/src/hobbit_launch/launch/HeadScripts/
scp headStart.sh pi@192.168.2.199:/home/pi/headStart.sh 
scp headKickStarter.sh pi@192.168.2.199:/home/pi/headKickStarter.sh 
scp activateHeadAutoStart.sh pi@192.168.2.199:/home/pi/activateHeadAutoStart.sh
scp owlpose.py pi@192.168.2.199:/home/pi/workspace/blue_owlpose/scripts/owlpose.py
scp herkulex.py pi@192.168.2.199:/home/pi/workspace/blue_owlpose/scripts/herkulex.py

ssh pi@192.168.2.199

chmod +x activateHeadAutoStart.sh && ./activateHeadAutoStart.sh

and then nano ~/.bashrc and put a # in front of the rosrun commands 

I literally cannot make it easier than this :)


Ammar
